imdb.title: Chiquititas
plot: The lives of a group of orphans who live in a manor known as Raio De Luz are touched and changed by a sweet-hearted, dedicated young woman.::Anonymous
synopsis: Carol is a sweet-hearted, dedicated young woman who join in the lives of a group of orphans that live in the Raio De Luz instituition. The place was raised by her employer José Ricardo Almeida Campos, in order to hide his granddaugther, whose mother Gabriela became mentally affected due to Ricardo's lies about the baby being stillborn. Gabriela's brother Júnior arrives from London and is horrified with her condition, blaming their father and bringing his supposed benevolences into question. At the Café Boutique, Júnior meets Carol and they fall for each other, for José Ricardo's angry since she is not at the same social level of the Almeida Campos family. They both help Mili, the lost daughter, in the search for her past. Mili and Júnior's interaction makes her close to Gabriela, and the girl softens her condition, both unaware of their blood ties. Mili's life, as well as her fellow Raio De Luz interns is then changed due to Carol's good actions, and she gradually becomes a "mother" for the "chiquititas".
